Both of them miss someone in their life, While it isn't directly stated (prob because hes to young to understand it really) Haru needs a mother in his life. Chiaki on the other hand misses her husband and obviously has feelings for him wich we can see on page 18 where only then she puts away her ring because Haru told her that he loved her, at that point she saw him as a replacement as both her husband and the child she never had, he was everything Chiaki wanted in one.
They are a perfect fit yet its so wrong because this isn't a relationship that can hold, it will deteriorate with age. Also i don't think she is a pedo, just a broken person.

After rereading this manga, I realized it's not so much of a forbidden relationship (though it does end up like that).  But rather a story of manipulation and usage of a child to deal with loneliness with sex and nurturing.   It's a story of a half victim: A lonely and fearful child fulfilled by a caring adoptive mother, but for the cost of his innocence.  Though weirdly, the child is more than aware of what kinda thing he's doing with her;he still keep having sex with her.  I keep thinking about the meaning, or rather, the theme of this manga.  This is just my two Cents, thanks for reading.
